### WeakMap — Private Class Data Without # Fields

Before ES2022 private class fields (`#field`), WeakMap was the idiomatic way to store truly private per-instance data.

```javascript
// --- Private data with WeakMap (pre-ES2022 pattern) ---
const _private = new WeakMap();

class BankAccount {
  constructor(owner, balance) {
    // Private state stored in WeakMap, not on the instance
    _private.set(this, { balance, transactions: [] });
    this.owner = owner; // public
  }

  deposit(amount) {
    const priv = _private.get(this);
    priv.balance += amount;
    priv.transactions.push({ type: 'deposit', amount, date: Date.now() });
  }

  getBalance() {
    return _private.get(this).balance;
  }

  getHistory() {
    return [..._private.get(this).transactions];
  }
}

const acc = new BankAccount('Alice', 1000);
acc.deposit(500);
console.log(acc.getBalance()); // 1500
// acc._private — undefined: no access from outside
// JSON.stringify(acc) — {"owner": "Alice"}: balance not serialized

// --- Modern equivalent with # fields ---
class ModernBankAccount {
  #balance;
  #transactions = [];

  constructor(owner, balance) {
    this.owner = owner;
    this.#balance = balance;
  }
  deposit(amount) {
    this.#balance += amount;
    this.#transactions.push({ amount, date: Date.now() });
  }
  getBalance() { return this.#balance; }
}

// --- WeakSet: membership tracking without memory leaks ---
const seen = new WeakSet();

function processOnce(obj) {
  if (seen.has(obj)) {
    console.log('Already processed, skipping');
    return;
  }
  seen.add(obj);
  // ... process
}

let item = { id: 42 };
processOnce(item); // processed
processOnce(item); // Already processed, skipping
item = null; // WeakSet doesn't prevent GC — item is cleaned up
```

**Common interview trap:** WeakMap vs Map for private data: the critical difference is memory. With `Map`, instances stored as keys are never GC'd even after all other references are gone — a classic memory leak. With WeakMap, when the instance is no longer referenced anywhere else, both the key and its associated private data are garbage collected. This is the entire point.

